file-name: XC512702-Tickell's Blue Flycatcher-calls-1-2-Xeno-Kledang-Sayong Forest Reserve, Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia-20th December 2019.mp3
rmk: I spent part of the morning listening to Tickell's Blue Flycatchers sing and call out. There were at least 3 birds (perhaps 3) with 2 separate adult males and one female. I made a number of recordings. This recording has songs and calls, a number of types interspersed. Apart from the classical song, the other types of call are a churring ‘trrt-trrt’ and an individual ‘tak’. Another type of call, made infrequently, is a sharp whistle like call.

file-name: XC512701-Tickell's Blue Flycatcher-calls-5-2-Xeno-Kledang-Sayong Forest Reserve, Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia-20th December 2019.mp3
rmk: I spent part of the morning listening to Tickell's Blue Flycatchers sing and call out. There were at least 3 birds (perhaps 3) with 2 separate adult males and one female. I made a number of recordings. The classical song comprises a “sweet song of 4-7 tinkling, metallic notes” (Wells 2007). It is highly variable and I think used as territorial marker. Note that there are 2 birds calling (2 sets of calls). The lower volumes ones were of a bird further away and the higher volume were the answering calls of the bird nearer to me. Here the notes appeared fixed (there were 8 calls and 8 responses in 50 seconds) but I have recorded other sonograms with varying song structure.
